<span id="freeTextContainer4450961983223662110">Morgan Llywelyn writes most often about Ireland. I love Ireland and reading about Irish history, especially ancient Ireland. It seems like the one country that really is out of a fairy tale. <br/><br/>I also love reading about the historical/mythical figures of Ireland&apos;s past - she makes them become very real. <br/><br/>Bard is the story of the &apos;founding&apos; of Ireland - well of those who we consider &apos;Irish&apos;. The Milesians come to the island and make contact with the Tuatha Da Danans...a mythical &apos;fairy&apos; race. This te</span>
  <span id="freeText4450961983223662110" style="display:none">Morgan Llywelyn writes most often about Ireland. I love Ireland and reading about Irish history, especially ancient Ireland. It seems like the one country that really is out of a fairy tale. <br /><br />I also love reading about the historical/mythical figures of Ireland's past - she makes them become very real. <br /><br />Bard is the story of the 'founding' of Ireland - well of those who we consider 'Irish'. The Milesians come to the island and make contact with the Tuatha Da Danans...a mythical 'fairy' race. This tells the story of their settling the island and making it their own.<br /><br /></span>
