<div id="review_2858847958" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2858847958" />
    <a title="Bish Denham" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5802258-bish-denham"><img alt="Bish Denham" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1442635219p2/5802258.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2858847958?book_show_action=true">Jul 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Bish Denham" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Bish Denham" href="/user/show/5802258-bish-denham">Bish Denham</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5802258-bish-denham?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/5802258-bish-denham?shelf=myth-legend">myth-legend</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2858847958" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer7713601328522943958">It was okay... I wanted to like this book a lot more than I did, particularly since the first paragraph and opening scene captured my heart and gave me chills and there were several times when the writing was very beautiful.<br/><br/>But... it dragged. It was a story that was told, more than shown. There didn&apos;t seem to be a focus on any one character. I think if the story had been told from Amergin&apos;s point of view, or moved between him and Shinann in Ireland, my attention would have been held. As it is, t</span>
  <span id="freeText7713601328522943958" style="display:none">It was okay... I wanted to like this book a lot more than I did, particularly since the first paragraph and opening scene captured my heart and gave me chills and there were several times when the writing was very beautiful.<br /><br />But... it dragged. It was a story that was told, more than shown. There didn't seem to be a focus on any one character. I think if the story had been told from Amergin's point of view, or moved between him and Shinann in Ireland, my attention would have been held. As it is, the author bounced around between characters (a choppy omniscient view) in such a way that I never got truly invested in any of the them, and I wanted to. I particularly wanted to be fully invested in Amergin the Bard. But he seemed to be as much victim of too much verbiage as all the other characters.<br /><br />Sigh. </span>
  <a data-text-id="7713601328522943958" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
